# pt-BR locale (not pt-PT)

**Always-on contract:** **`.cursor/rules/docs-locale-pt-br-contract.mdc`** — assistants must default to **pt-BR** for all Portuguese prose unless an exception there applies. This file is the **expanded** prefer/avoid table and workflow notes.

**Audience:** Operators and prospects in **Brazil** first; **English** remains the global lingua franca for paths, commits, APIs, and many technical terms.

**Operator chat:** When the operator writes in Portuguese, replies follow the **same** vocabulary and style bar — see **`.cursor/rules/operator-chat-language-pt-br.mdc`** (always applied) and **`.cursor/skills/operator-dialogue-pt-br/SKILL.md`**.

**Scope beyond `*.pt_BR.md`:** Portuguese text in **gitignored** operator paths (e.g. **`docs/private/social_drafts/drafts/*.md`** and **`editorial/*.md`**, private runbooks) should still read **Brazilian**, not European Portuguese—same table below. Automated tests may not scan those paths; assistants **enforce by habit**. Draft filenames use **`YYYY-MM-DD`** prefix per private **`editorial/SOCIAL_HUB.md`** (publication vs planned date).

**English-only prose:** When a document or section is **explicitly EN** (not a pt-BR mirror), **`en-US`** is the preferred register for narrative copy unless the repo already standardizes otherwise.

## Prefer (pt-BR) vs avoid (typical pt-PT)

| Prefer                                | Avoid                                                  |
| --------                              | --------                                               |
| arquivo                               | ficheiro                                               |
| compartilhar / compartilhamento       | partilhar / partilha                                   |
| seção                                 | secção                                                 |
| ações (if needed)                     | acções                                                 |
| usuário                               | utilizador                                             |
| atualizar                             | actualizar                                             |
| artefato(s)                           | artefacto(s)                                           |
| registro(s) (documento, prontuário)   | registo(s) (mesmo sentido)                             |
| assinatura (SaaS / licença)           | subscrição                                             |
| acessa / acessam                      | acede / acedem                                         |
| console (DevTools, UI)                | consola                                                |
| equipe                                | equipa                                                 |
| precisa / tem que / deve (obligation) | tem de                                                 |
| continua usando / continua precisando | continua a usar / continua a precisar                  |
| falhando (not “X a falhar”)           | … a falhar                                             |
| gerenciador de senhas                 | gestor de senhas (optional; BR often uses gerenciador) |

Keep **English** for commands, product names, and jargon where the repo already does (e.g. `docker prune`, **Bitwarden**, **Teams**).

## Automation

- After substantive **pt-BR** edits (not only `*.pt_BR.md` — any Portuguese-heavy ops copy), run:
- **`uv run pytest tests/test_markdown_lint.py::test_markdown_lint_no_violations tests/test_docs_pt_br_locale.py -q`**
- Run **`uv run pytest tests/test_docs_pt_br_locale.py -v`** after large doc edits. The scan includes all **`*.pt_BR.md`** under the repo; extend **`tests/test_docs_pt_br_locale.py`** (`_extra_locale_scan_paths`) if a mixed-language file should be guarded the same way.
- Extend **`_extra_locale_scan_paths`** if **`docs/private/pitch/slides.yaml`** or website copy becomes tracked and includes pt-BR strings.
- **Gitignored** Portuguese in **`docs/private/social_drafts/`** is not scanned on CI; a **tracked mirror** under **`docs/private.example/social_drafts/*.example.md`** (kept in sync by hand) is listed in **`_extra_locale_scan_paths`** — see **`drafts/2026-04-08_instagram_databoar_patreon_apoio_oss.example.md`**.
- **Skills / rules to keep aligned:** **`.cursor/rules/docs-policy.mdc`**, **`.cursor/skills/documentation-en-pt-br/SKILL.md`**, **`.cursor/rules/operator-chat-language-pt-br.mdc`** (dialogue + same lexical bar as docs). **Termos técnicos, jargão e nomes próprios em inglês** são aceitáveis quando o repositório já usa assim — código-switch EN/pt-BR não é problema.

